Dataset overview :¶

Dataset :

The original dataset contains around (100 Thousands) loan-records for a certain american bank from 2009 to 2013.

Investigation overview :¶

Investigation :

The analysis process will focus on fundamental aspects of the data provided, answering obvious questions and through the presentation progress, we will be answering more complex questions.

Some of these questions are:

Which year, month and day were preferred by loaners ?
What are loaners segments and how much they contribute to the total figures ?
How to increase the loan sums of the bank ?
What segments of loaners the bank should focus on?
and more...

Observations :


Graph 1&2 show that the last quarter of the year had the highest loans rates (october is the hightest) while the first quarter of the year had the lowest loan rates (february is the lowest). we observe a slight increase in loans counts as we push toward the end of the year, (interval: 3-months graph) shows that more clearly.

Graph 3&4 show that the last-5 days of the month had the highest loans rates (day-30 is the hightest) while the first-5 days of the month had the lowest loan rates (day-1 is the lowest). we observe a slight increase in loans rates as we push toward the end of the month, the (interval: 5-days graph) shows that more clearly.
